## Commands

```bash
make run            # print pipeline config
make setup-source   # clone OrcaArch engine into .orcaarch/source
make test           # run full test suite
make reports        # generate CSV reports in ./output
make api            # start read-only API on localhost:8080
make bench          # run benchmarks
make wac            # run reports (WAC is part of the pipeline)
make clean          # remove ./output and .orcaarch/source
make help           # list all targets
```

## Output

`make reports` generates:

```
output/reconciliation.csv
output/ledger.csv
output/risk.csv
```

`make api` starts the API at `localhost:8080`:

```bash
curl -s localhost:8080/api/v1/reports/inventory | head -c 300
curl -s localhost:8080/api/v1/reports/ledger | head -c 300
curl -s localhost:8080/api/v1/reports/risk | head -c 300
```

Press `Ctrl+C` to stop the API.

